OL,7,FHe was accused of stealing #33,000
OL,8,Ffrom his post office and pleaded
OL,9,Fguilty, despite knowing he was
OL,10,Finnocent.
OL,12,FHe says the stigma of his conviction
OL,13,Fand the debt that accompanied it left
OL,14,Fhim with no option but to emigrate.
OL,16,FHe now lives in a friend's house in
OL,17,FPortugal, where he was relieved to
OL,18,Frecently be exonerated, having
OL,19,Freceived a letter.
